{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28ce6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"300ff–111"},"text":"§ 300ff–111.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" HIV/AIDS communities, schools, and centers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28ce7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Schools; centers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28ce8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may make grants and enter into contracts to assist public and nonprofit private entities and schools and academic health science centers in meeting the costs of projects—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28ce9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to train health personnel, including practitioners in programs under this subchapter and other community providers, in the diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of HIV/AIDS, including the prevention of the perinatal transmission of the disease, including measures for the prevention and treatment of opportunistic infections, and including (as applicable to the type of health professional involved), prenatal and other gynecological care for women with HIV/AIDS;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cea-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to train the faculty of schools of, and graduate departments or programs of, medicine, nursing, osteopathic medicine, dentistry, public health, allied health, and mental health practice to teach health professions students to provide for the health care needs of individuals with HIV/AIDS;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28ceb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to develop and disseminate curricula and resource materials relating to the care and treatment of individuals with such disease and the prevention of the disease among individuals who are at risk of contracting the disease; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cec-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to develop protocols for the medical care of women with HIV/AIDS, including prenatal and other gynecological care for such women.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28ced-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Preference in making grants","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In making grants under paragraph (1), the Secretary shall give preference to qualified projects which will—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cee-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" train, or result in the training of, health professionals who will provide treatment for minority individuals and Native Americans with HIV/AIDS and other individuals who are at high risk of contracting such disease;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cef-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" train, or result in the training of, minority health professionals and minority allied health professionals to provide treatment for individuals with such disease; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" train or result in the training of health professionals and allied health professionals to provide treatment for hepatitis B or C co-infected individuals.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Application","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No grant or contract may be made under paragraph (1) unless an application is submitted to the Secretary in such form, at such time, and containing such information, as the Secretary may prescribe.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Dental schools","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Grants","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may make grants to dental schools and programs described in subparagraph (B) to assist such schools and programs with respect to oral health care to patients with HIV/AIDS.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Eligible applicants","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this subsection, the dental schools and programs referred to in this subparagraph are dental schools and programs that were described in section 294","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":"(b)(4)(B) of this title as such section was in effect on the day before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-11-13"},"text":"November 13, 1998","children":[],"tail":", and in addition dental hygiene programs that are accredited by the Commission on Dental Accreditation."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Application","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Each dental school or program described in section ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002439"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002439"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original."}],"tail":" the section referred to in paragraph (1)(B) may annually submit an application documenting the unreimbursed costs of oral health care provided to patients with HIV/AIDS by that school or hospital during the prior year."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Distribution","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall distribute the available funds among all eligible applicants, taking into account the number of patients with HIV/AIDS served and the unreimbursed oral health care costs incurred by each institution as compared with the total number of patients served and costs incurred by all eligible applicants.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Maintenance of effort","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall not make a grant under this subsection if doing so would result in any reduction in State funding allotted for such purposes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cf9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/b/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Community-based care","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may make grants to dental schools and programs described in paragraph (1)(B) that partner with community-based dentists to provide oral health care to patients with HIV/AIDS in unserved areas. Such partnerships shall permit the training of dental students and residents and the participation of community dentists as adjunct faculty.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cfa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cfb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Schools; centers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of awarding grants under subsection (a), there are authorized to be appropriated $34,700,000 for each of the fiscal years 2007 through 2009, $36,535,000 for fiscal year 2010, $38,257,000 for fiscal year 2011, $40,170,000 for fiscal year 2012, and $42,178,000 for fiscal year 2013.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cfc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–111/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Dental schools","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of awarding grants under subsection (b), there are authorized to be appropriated $13,000,000 for each of the fiscal years 2007 through 2009, $13,650,000 for fiscal year 2010, $14,333,000 for fiscal year 2011, $15,049,000 for fiscal year 2012, and $15,802,000 for fiscal year 2013.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28cfd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373"},"text":"July 1, 1944, ch. 373","children":[],"tail":", title XXVI, § 2692, formerly title VII, § 776, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/408/tI/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–408, title I, § 102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/2050"},"text":"106 Stat. 2050","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/531/tIII/s313/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–531, title III, § 313(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/3507"},"text":"106 Stat. 3507","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered title XXVI, § 2692, and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/146/s3/h"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–146, § 3(h)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-05-20"},"text":"May 20, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1363"},"text":"110 Stat. 1363","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/166/s5/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–166, § 5(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-07-29"},"text":"July 29, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1449"},"text":"110 Stat. 1449","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/345/tIV/s402/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–345, title IV, § 402(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (b), (c), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-20"},"text":"Oct. 20, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1348"},"text":"114 Stat. 1348","children":[],"tail":", 1349; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/415/tVI/s602"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–415, title VI, § 602","children":[],"tail":", title VII, §§ 702(3), 703, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2817"},"text":"120 Stat. 2817","children":[],"tail":", 2820; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/87/s2/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–87, § 2(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3)(A), (f)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/2885"},"text":"123 Stat. 2885","children":[],"tail":", 2886.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb6a28cfe-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb6a28cff-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb6a28d00-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s294n"},"text":"section 294n of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to renumbering by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/146"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–146","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb6a28d01-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2009—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/87/s2/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–87, § 2(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3)(A), repealed "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/415/s703"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–415, § 703","children":[],"tail":", and revived the provisions of this section as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 2009","children":[],"tail":". See 2006 Amendment note and Effective Date of 2009 Amendment; Revival of Section note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/87/s2/f/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–87, § 2(f)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “are authorized” for “is authorized” and inserted “, $36,535,000 for fiscal year 2010, $38,257,000 for fiscal year 2011, $40,170,000 for fiscal year 2012, and $42,178,000 for fiscal year 2013” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/87/s2/f/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–87, § 2(f)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “are authorized” for “is authorized” and inserted “, $13,650,000 for fiscal year 2010, $14,333,000 for fiscal year 2011, $15,049,000 for fiscal year 2012, and $15,802,000 for fiscal year 2013” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/415/s703"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–415, § 703","children":[],"tail":", which directed repeal of this section effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2009","children":[],"tail":", was itself repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/87/s2/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–87, § 2(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 2009","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/415/s702/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–415, § 702(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “HIV/AIDS” for “HIV disease” wherever appearing in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/415/s602/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–415, § 602(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “and Native Americans” after “minority individuals”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/415/s602/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–415, § 602(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", (2), (3), added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/415/s602/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–415, § 602(b)","children":[],"tail":", reenacted heading without change and amended text generally, substituting provisions authorizing appropriations for fiscal years 2007 through 2009 for provisions authorizing appropriations for fiscal years 2001 through 2005."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (a)(1)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/345/s402/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–345, § 402(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “to train” for “training”, substituted “, including” for “and including” after “transmission of the disease”, and inserted “, and including (as applicable to the type of health professional involved), prenatal and other gynecological care for women with HIV disease” before semicolon at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1)(D). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/345/s402/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–345, § 402(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":"–(D), added subpar. (D)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/345/s402/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–345, § 402(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", amended heading and text of par. (1) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary may make grants to assist dental schools and programs described in section 294"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":"(b)(4)(B) of this title with respect to oral health care to patients with HIV disease.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/345/s402/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–345, § 402(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the section referred to in paragraph (1)(B)” for “294"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":"(b)(4)(B) of this title”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/345/s402/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–345, § 402(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (5)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/345/s402/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–345, § 402(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “fiscal years 2001 through 2005” for “fiscal years 1996 through 2000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/345/s402/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–345, § 402(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", amended heading and text of par. (2) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “For the purpose of grants under subsection (b) of this section, there are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary for each of the fiscal years 1996 through 2000.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/146/s3/h/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–146, § 3(h)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2)(A), substituted “HIV/AIDS communities, schools, and centers” for “Acquired immune deficiency syndrome” as section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/166/s5/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–166, § 5(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “in programs under this subchapter” for “in subchapter XXIV programs” and struck out “infection and” after “prevention of HIV”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/146/s3/h/2/B/iii"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–146, § 3(h)(2)(B)(iii)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (A). Former subpar. (A) redesignated (B)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/146/s3/h/2/B/iv"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–146, § 3(h)(2)(B)(iv)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “and” after semicolon."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/146/s3/h/2/B/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–146, § 3(h)(2)(B)(i)","children":[],"tail":", (ii), redesignated subpar. (A) as (B) and struck out former subpar. (B) which read as follows: “to train practitioners to provide for the health care needs of such individuals;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1)(C), (D). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/146/s3/h/2/B/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–146, § 3(h)(2)(B)(i)","children":[],"tail":", (ii), redesignated subpar. (D) as (C) and struck out former subpar. (C) which read as follows: “with respect to improving clinical skills in the diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of such disease, to educate and train the health professionals and clinical staff of schools of medicine, osteopathic medicine, and dentistry; and”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/166/s5/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–166, § 5(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c) and struck out heading and text of former subsec. (c). Text read as follows: “For purposes of this section:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) The term ‘HIV disease’ means infection with the human immunodeficiency virus, and includes any condition arising from such infection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) The term ‘human immunodeficiency virus’ means the etiologic agent for acquired immune deficiency syndrome.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/166/s5/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–166, § 5(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out heading and text of subsec. (d) relating to authorization of appropriations for fiscal years 1996 through 2000. Text read as follows: “There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out this section, such sums as may be necessary for each of the fiscal years 1996 through 2000.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/166/s5/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–166, § 5(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out heading and text of subsec. (d) relating to authorization of appropriations for fiscal years 1993 through 1995. Text read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Schools; centers","children":[],"tail":".—For the purpose of grants under subsection (a) of this section, there is authorized to be appropriated $23,000,000 for each of the fiscal years 1993 through 1995."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Dental schools","children":[],"tail":".—For the purpose of grants under subsection (b) of this section, there is authorized to be appropriated $7,000,000 for each of the fiscal years 1993 through 1995.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/146/s3/h/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–146, § 3(h)(4)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d) relating to authorization of appropriations for fiscal years 1996 through 2000."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/531"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–531","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “No grant” for “no grant” in par. (3), could not be executed because the words “no grant” did not appear in par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb6a4d5f2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb6a4d5f3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2009 Amendment; Revival of Sec